		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Ring - Legendary (Requires Attunement)</em></p><p><em>Rings of Djinni Summoning are often created by the djinn they summon and given to mortals as gifts of friendship or tokens of esteem.</em></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - Concentration (1 Hour) - 24 Hours</p><p><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>While wearing this ring, you can summon a particular <strong>@UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.actors24.Actor.mmDjinni00000000]{Djinni}</strong> from the Elemental Plane of Air. The djinni appears in an unoccupied space you choose within 120 feet of yourself and remains as long as you maintain Concentrationor until it drops to 0 Hit Points.</p></li><li><p>While summoned, the djinni is friendly to you and your allies and obeys your commands. If you issue no commands, it defends itself but takes no other actions.</p></li><li><p>The ring becomes nonmagical if the djinni dies.</p></li></ul>",
